{
  "video_id": "FauPVZxDXxk",
  "title": "Why I still have hope for coral reefs | Kristen Marhaver",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12746.0,
      "end_time": 15170.0,
      "text": "The first time I cried underwater"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15194.0,
      "end_time": 16737.0,
      "text": "was in 2008,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 16761.0,
      "end_time": 18338.0,
      "text": "the island of Curaçao,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18362.0,
      "end_time": 20244.0,
      "text": "way down in the southern Caribbean."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 20668.0,
      "end_time": 22320.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s beautiful there."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 22344.0,
      "end_time": 25270.0,
      "text": "I was studying these corals for my PhD,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 25294.0,
      "end_time": 27676.0,
      "text": "and after days and days of diving on the same reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 27700.0,
      "end_time": 29729.0,
      "text": "I had gotten to know them as individuals."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29753.0,
      "end_time": 32224.0,
      "text": "I had made friends with coral colonies --"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 32247.0,
      "end_time": 34100.0,
      "text": "totally a normal thing to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 35800.0,
      "end_time": 39775.0,
      "text": "Then, Hurricane Omar smashed them apart and ripped off their skin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39800.0,
      "end_time": 44288.0,
      "text": "leaving little bits of wounded tissue that would have a hard time healing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44313.0,
      "end_time": 47620.0,
      "text": "and big patches of dead skeleton that would get overgrown by algae."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 48201.0,
      "end_time": 50225.0,
      "text": "When I saw this damage for the first time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50249.0,
      "end_time": 52590.0,
      "text": "stretching all the way down the reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52830.0,
      "end_time": 53940.0,
      "text": "I sunk onto the sand in my scuba gear"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53964.0,
      "end_time": 55360.0,
      "text": "and I cried."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55384.0,
      "end_time": 57741.0,
      "text": "If a coral could die that fast,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57765.0,
      "end_time": 59654.0,
      "text": "how could a reef ever survive?"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60174.0,
      "end_time": 63133.0,
      "text": "And why was I making it my job to try to fight for them?"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63672.0,
      "end_time": 66704.0,
      "text": "I never heard another scientist tell that kind of story"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 66728.0,
      "end_time": 68940.0,
      "text": "until last year."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68623.0,
      "end_time": 70628.0,
      "text": "A scientist in Guam wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 70652.0,
      "end_time": 72199.0,
      "text": "\"I cried right into my mask,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 72223.0,
      "end_time": 74433.0,
      "text": "seeing the damage on the reefs."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 75469.0,
      "end_time": 77410.0,
      "text": "Then a scientist in Australia wrote,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 77434.0,
      "end_time": 80431.0,
      "text": "\"I showed my students the results of our coral surveys,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 80455.0,
      "end_time": 81807.0,
      "text": "and we wept.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 82716.0,
      "end_time": 85363.0,
      "text": "Crying about corals is having a moment, guys."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 85388.0,
      "end_time": 86522.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 86546.0,
      "end_time": 88490.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s because reefs in the Pacific"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88514.0,
      "end_time": 91348.0,
      "text": "are losing corals faster than we&#39;ve ever seen before."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 91689.0,
      "end_time": 92961.0,
      "text": "Because of climate change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 92985.0,
      "end_time": 95794.0,
      "text": "the water is so hot for so long in the summers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 95818.0,
      "end_time": 97993.0,
      "text": "that these animals can&#39;t function normally."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 98494.0,
      "end_time": 101522.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re spitting out the colored algae that lives in their skin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 101546.0,
      "end_time": 106611.0,
      "text": "and the clear bleached tissue that&#39;s left usually starves to death"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 106635.0,
      "end_time": 107889.0,
      "text": "and then rots away."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 108944.0,
      "end_time": 111307.0,
      "text": "Then the skeletons are overgrown by algae."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 111781.0,
      "end_time": 114104.0,
      "text": "This is happening over an unbelievable scale."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 114128.0,
      "end_time": 118264.0,
      "text": "The Northern Great Barrier Reef lost two-thirds of its corals last year"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 118288.0,
      "end_time": 120843.0,
      "text": "over a distance of hundreds of miles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 120867.0,
      "end_time": 122669.0,
      "text": "then bleached again this year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 122693.0,
      "end_time": 124811.0,
      "text": "and the bleaching stretched further south."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 125824.0,
      "end_time": 128138.0,
      "text": "Reefs in the Pacific are in a nosedive right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 128162.0,
      "end_time": 130701.0,
      "text": "and no one knows how bad it&#39;s going to get,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 130725.0,
      "end_time": 132940.0,
      "text": "except ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 132118.0,
      "end_time": 134570.0,
      "text": "over in the Caribbean where I work,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 134810.0,
      "end_time": 136159.0,
      "text": "we&#39;ve already been through the nosedive."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 136519.0,
      "end_time": 140463.0,
      "text": "Reefs there have suffered through centuries of intense human abuse."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 140764.0,
      "end_time": 142947.0,
      "text": "We kind of already know how the story goes."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 143283.0,
      "end_time": 147108.0,
      "text": "And we might be able to help predict what happens next."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 147774.0,
      "end_time": 149349.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s consult a graph."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 152442.0,
      "end_time": 153823.0,
      "text": "Since the invention of scuba,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 153847.0,
      "end_time": 156828.0,
      "text": "scientists have measured the amount of coral on the seafloor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 156852.0,
      "end_time": 158518.0,
      "text": "and how it&#39;s changed through time."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 159216.0,
      "end_time": 161677.0,
      "text": "And after centuries of ratcheting human pressure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 161701.0,
      "end_time": 164302.0,
      "text": "Caribbean reefs met one of three fates."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 164774.0,
      "end_time": 167200.0,
      "text": "Some reefs lost their corals very quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 169650.0,
      "end_time": 172509.0,
      "text": "Some reefs lost their corals more slowly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 172533.0,
      "end_time": 175525.0,
      "text": "but kind of ended up in the same place."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 175550.0,
      "end_time": 177487.0,
      "text": "OK, so far this is not going very well."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 178640.0,
      "end_time": 180327.0,
      "text": "But some reefs in the Caribbean --"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 180351.0,
      "end_time": 182244.0,
      "text": "the ones best protected"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 182268.0,
      "end_time": 184982.0,
      "text": "and the ones a little further from humans --"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 185600.0,
      "end_time": 188547.0,
      "text": "they managed to hold onto their corals."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 189227.0,
      "end_time": 190710.0,
      "text": "Give us a challenge."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 191909.0,
      "end_time": 194565.0,
      "text": "And, we almost never saw a reef hit zero."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 196110.0,
      "end_time": 198596.0,
      "text": "The second time I cried underwater"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 198620.0,
      "end_time": 202300.0,
      "text": "was on the north shore of Curaçao, 2011."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 202540.0,
      "end_time": 203738.0,
      "text": "It was the calmest day of the year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 203762.0,
      "end_time": 206131.0,
      "text": "but it&#39;s always pretty sketchy diving there."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 206155.0,
      "end_time": 208251.0,
      "text": "My boyfriend and I swam against the waves."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 208275.0,
      "end_time": 210949.0,
      "text": "I watched my compass so we could find our way back out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 210973.0,
      "end_time": 212603.0,
      "text": "and he watched for sharks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 212627.0,
      "end_time": 215483.0,
      "text": "and after 20 minutes of swimming that felt like an hour,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 215507.0,
      "end_time": 217223.0,
      "text": "we finally dropped down to the reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 217247.0,
      "end_time": 218806.0,
      "text": "and I was so shocked,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 218830.0,
      "end_time": 220476.0,
      "text": "and I was so happy"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 220500.0,
      "end_time": 222495.0,
      "text": "that my eyes filled with tears."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 223219.0,
      "end_time": 228144.0,
      "text": "There were corals 1,000 years old lined up one after another."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 228996.0,
      "end_time": 233682.0,
      "text": "They had survived the entire history of European colonialism in the Caribbean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 233706.0,
      "end_time": 235840.0,
      "text": "and for centuries before that."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 237465.0,
      "end_time": 241623.0,
      "text": "I never knew what a coral could do when it was given a chance to thrive."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 242660.0,
      "end_time": 246430.0,
      "text": "The truth is that even as we lose so many corals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 246670.0,
      "end_time": 249123.0,
      "text": "even as we go through this massive coral die-off,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 249147.0,
      "end_time": 250998.0,
      "text": "some reefs will survive."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 251732.0,
      "end_time": 253386.0,
      "text": "Some will be ragged on the edge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 253410.0,
      "end_time": 255299.0,
      "text": "some will be beautiful."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 255911.0,
      "end_time": 258601.0,
      "text": "And by protecting shorelines and giving us food to eat"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 258625.0,
      "end_time": 260375.0,
      "text": "and supporting tourism,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 260399.0,
      "end_time": 263521.0,
      "text": "they will still be worth billions and billions of dollars a year."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 264430.0,
      "end_time": 266634.0,
      "text": "The best time to protect a reef was 50 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 266658.0,
      "end_time": 269576.0,
      "text": "but the second-best time is right now."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 271115.0,
      "end_time": 273660.0,
      "text": "Even as we go through bleaching events,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 273900.0,
      "end_time": 275633.0,
      "text": "more frequent and in more places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 275657.0,
      "end_time": 277931.0,
      "text": "some corals will be able to recover."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 278792.0,
      "end_time": 281643.0,
      "text": "We had a bleaching event in 2010 in the Caribbean"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 281668.0,
      "end_time": 285253.0,
      "text": "that took off big patches of skin on boulder corals like these."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 286172.0,
      "end_time": 288785.0,
      "text": "This coral lost half of its skin."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 288809.0,
      "end_time": 293360.0,
      "text": "But if you look at the side of this coral a few years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 293600.0,
      "end_time": 295408.0,
      "text": "this coral is actually healthy again."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 295432.0,
      "end_time": 297729.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s doing what a healthy coral does."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 297753.0,
      "end_time": 299851.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s making copies of its polyps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 299875.0,
      "end_time": 301330.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s fighting back the algae"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 301354.0,
      "end_time": 303126.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s reclaiming its territory."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 304195.0,
      "end_time": 305360.0,
      "text": "If a few polyps survive,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 305384.0,
      "end_time": 306557.0,
      "text": "a coral can regrow;"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 306581.0,
      "end_time": 310686.0,
      "text": "it just needs time and protection and a reasonable temperature."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 311188.0,
      "end_time": 312997.0,
      "text": "Some corals can regrow in 10 years --"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 313210.0,
      "end_time": 314744.0,
      "text": "others take a lot longer."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 314768.0,
      "end_time": 317419.0,
      "text": "But the more stresses we take off them locally --"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 317443.0,
      "end_time": 321437.0,
      "text": "things like overfishing, sewage pollution, fertilizer pollution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 321461.0,
      "end_time": 323906.0,
      "text": "dredging, coastal construction --"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 323930.0,
      "end_time": 326800.0,
      "text": "the better they can hang on as we stabilize the climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 326824.0,
      "end_time": 328634.0,
      "text": "and the faster they can regrow."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 329766.0,
      "end_time": 333504.0,
      "text": "And as we go through the long, tough and necessary process"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 333528.0,
      "end_time": 336133.0,
      "text": "of stabilizing the climate of planet Earth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 336157.0,
      "end_time": 338587.0,
      "text": "some new corals will still be born."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 339143.0,
      "end_time": 341490.0,
      "text": "This is what I study in my research."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 341498.0,
      "end_time": 344450.0,
      "text": "We try to understand how corals make babies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 344690.0,
      "end_time": 346743.0,
      "text": "and how those babies find their way to the reef,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 346767.0,
      "end_time": 349690.0,
      "text": "and we invent new methods to help them survive"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 349930.0,
      "end_time": 351260.0,
      "text": "those early, fragile life stages."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 351904.0,
      "end_time": 354905.0,
      "text": "One of my favorite coral babies of all time"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 354929.0,
      "end_time": 356938.0,
      "text": "showed up right after Hurricane Omar."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 356963.0,
      "end_time": 359654.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the same species I was studying before the storm,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 359678.0,
      "end_time": 362110.0,
      "text": "but you almost never see babies of this species --"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 362134.0,
      "end_time": 363349.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s really rare."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 363373.0,
      "end_time": 365687.0,
      "text": "This is actually an endangered species."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 366219.0,
      "end_time": 369715.0,
      "text": "In this photo, this little baby coral, this little circle of polyps,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 369739.0,
      "end_time": 371162.0,
      "text": "is a few years old."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 371616.0,
      "end_time": 373850.0,
      "text": "Like its cousins that bleach,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 373109.0,
      "end_time": 374945.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s fighting back the algae."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 374969.0,
      "end_time": 376894.0,
      "text": "And like its cousins on the north shore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 376918.0,
      "end_time": 379959.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s aiming to live for 1,000 years."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 381180.0,
      "end_time": 383868.0,
      "text": "What&#39;s happening in the world and in the ocean"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 383892.0,
      "end_time": 385690.0,
      "text": "has changed our time horizon."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 386457.0,
      "end_time": 389496.0,
      "text": "We can be incredibly pessimistic on the short term,"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 389520.0,
      "end_time": 390835.0,
      "text": "and mourn what we lost"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 390859.0,
      "end_time": 393524.0,
      "text": "and what we really took for granted."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 394280.0,
      "end_time": 396778.0,
      "text": "But we can still be optimistic on the long term,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 396802.0,
      "end_time": 399280.0,
      "text": "and we can still be ambitious about what we fight for"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 399304.0,
      "end_time": 402402.0,
      "text": "and what we expect from our governments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 402426.0,
      "end_time": 403717.0,
      "text": "from our planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 404364.0,
      "end_time": 408940.0,
      "text": "Corals have been living on planet Earth for hundreds of millions of years."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 408118.0,
      "end_time": 410311.0,
      "text": "They survived the extinction of the dinosaurs."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 410335.0,
      "end_time": 411599.0,
      "text": "They&#39;re badasses."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 412189.0,
      "end_time": 413666.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 413690.0,
      "end_time": 418229.0,
      "text": "An individual coral can go through tremendous trauma and fully recover"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 418253.0,
      "end_time": 421390.0,
      "text": "if it&#39;s given a chance and it&#39;s given protection."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 422420.0,
      "end_time": 424871.0,
      "text": "Corals have always been playing the long game,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 425539.0,
      "end_time": 426961.0,
      "text": "and now so are we."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 427612.0,
      "end_time": 428765.0,
      "text": "Thanks very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 428789.0,
      "end_time": 431637.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}